483
00:52:56,885 --> 00:53:14,009
Yes, one of the core teachings of the Buddha is the role of intention.

484
00:53:15,030 --> 00:53:17,052
Everything begins with your intention.

485
00:53:17,590 --> 00:53:20,313
An intention you can describe as a desire or a wish.

486
00:53:20,454 --> 00:53:22,297
It's a movement in the mind of wanting.

487
00:53:23,157 --> 00:53:26,362
If that's unwholesome, it's going to create an unwholesome conditioning.

488
00:53:27,284 --> 00:53:30,128
If it's wholesome, it'll create a wholesome conditioning.

489
00:53:30,148 --> 00:53:33,072
This is where your true karma lies in Buddhist understanding.

490
00:53:33,572 --> 00:53:45,150
What happens, you put an action out in the world, what comes to you from the world is being, you can't say that's your true karma because it's been messed about with by all these other people in the world.

491
00:53:45,130 --> 00:53:50,047
What you get back may be inappropriate to your original action.

492
00:53:51,130 --> 00:53:57,773
For instance, you may go to a lottery and buy a pound worth and you win 10 million.

493
00:53:58,445 --> 00:53:59,447
That's not your karma.

494
00:54:00,228 --> 00:54:04,775
That happens to be part of the whole system of joining a lottery.

495
00:54:05,898 --> 00:54:16,617
And if you have an understanding, oh well, in my past life I must have given thousands and thousands of pounds away, you're just rationalizing something which is a perfectly ordinary, you can put a straightforward rational argument to it.

496
00:54:17,197 --> 00:54:22,748
On the other hand, you might do some good and the person hates you for it and continues to hate you for it.

497
00:54:23,199 --> 00:54:24,320
And that's it.

498
00:54:24,360 --> 00:54:25,182
That's their problem.

499
00:54:25,882 --> 00:54:34,474
Real karma, in terms of the liberation of the heart, in terms of achieving this pure peace and happiness, is within ourselves.

500
00:54:34,815 --> 00:54:40,581
So when we intend something, it's important to recognize, is this going to do me good or bad?

501
00:54:41,543 --> 00:54:46,710
And remember that when you pay attention, it's an act of intention.

502
00:54:48,090 --> 00:54:52,237
Every time you pass a billboard on the bus and you look at it, it goes in.

503
00:54:52,418 --> 00:54:53,139
It's conditioning you.

504
00:54:53,780 --> 00:54:57,125
Because you've made an intention to actually attend to it.

505
00:54:58,166 --> 00:54:58,746
See?

506
00:54:58,766 --> 00:55:04,856
So that's why your intention is the beginning of your conditioning.

507
00:55:05,717 --> 00:55:13,710
So having recognized that this intention is a good intention, you then empower it and go into the action.

508
00:55:14,179 --> 00:55:40,726
as you go into the action you may be aware of yourself doing what you're doing but as your concentration grows and your commitment grows you lose yourself in the action that is you know you can call it an Ibanic moment ask yourself when you finish that ask yourself how was I in that moment you'll see there's no suffering there was peace there was happiness

509
00:55:43,119 --> 00:55:48,969
Now, if you go into a situation with indulgence, it's exactly the same.

